                         Midnight\n                                                         AM              PM\n\n\n"}, "is_active": true, "auto_gradable": true, "difficulty": 3, "explanation": null}, {"id": "cap-108-english-reading-032", "exam_id": "cap", "subject_id": "sub-cap-english-reading", "paper_id": "cap-108-english-reading", "question_type": "single_choice", "question_text": "Four people read the news and wrote what they thought about it.\nMike                                                        Jan 16 8:26 pm\nThe best time to drink coffee is when you want to drink coffee.\nSarah                                                             Jan 16 8:43 pm\nI usually wake up AFTER I drink coffee!\nCharlie                                                           Jan 16 8:59 pm\nThe worst time to drink coffee is when you''re DEAD.\nLisa                                                         Jan 16 9:18 pm\nIf you need someone to tell you when to drink coffee, well, that’s just sad.\nWhat did they think about the news?", "options": ["They wanted to try what it said.", "They were sad about what it said.", "They did not agree with what it said.", "They were not surprised at what it said."], "correct_answer": 2, "correct_answer_json": null, "parent_question_id": "cap-108-english-reading-passage-29", "media": null, "source": "official", "source_meta": {"parser_version": "cap_v0.1", "merger_version": "cap_merger_v0.2", "parsed_at": "2026-04-25T19:26:39+00:00", "source_pdf_sha1": "c53c93460131", "answer_pdf_sha1": "71bcc8be1a46", "flags": [], "parse_confidence": 1.0, "original_question_number": 32, "raw_text": "32. Four people read the news and wrote what they thought about it.\n\n\n\n\n       Mike                                                        Jan 16 8:26 pm\n       The best time to drink coffee is when you want to drink coffee.\n       Sarah                                                             Jan 16 8:43 pm\n       I usually wake up AFTER I drink coffee!\n       Charlie                                                           Jan 16 8:59 pm\n       The worst time to drink coffee is when you''re DEAD.\n       Lisa                                                         Jan 16 9:18 pm\n       If you need someone to tell you when to drink coffee, well, that’s just sad.\n\n\n    What did they think about the news?\n    (A) They wanted to try what it said.\n    (B) They were sad about what it said.\n    (C) They did not agree with what it said.\n    (D) They were not surprised at what it said.\n\n\n\n\n"}, "is_active": true, "auto_gradable": true, "difficulty": 3, "explanation": null}, {"id": "cap-108-english-reading-033", "exam_id": "cap", "subject_id": "sub-cap-english-reading", "paper_id": "cap-108-english-reading", "question_type": "single_choice", "question_text": "What does the report NOT suggest?", "options": ["Having more free buses for shoppers.  suggest 建議", "Changing the opening hours on weekdays.", "Making plans to help weekday morning business.", "Changing the time of the special sale on weekends."], "correct_answer": 2, "correct_answer_json": null, "parent_question_id": "cap-108-english-reading-passage-33", "media": null, "source": "official", "source_meta": {"parser_version": "cap_v0.1", "merger_version": "cap_merger_v0.2", "parsed_at": "2026-04-25T19:26:39+00:00", "source_pdf_sha1": "c53c93460131", "answer_pdf_sha1": "71bcc8be1a46", "flags": [], "parse_confidence": 1.0, "original_question_number": 33, "raw_text": "33. What does the report NOT suggest?\n    (A) Having more free buses for shoppers.\n                                                                    suggest 建議\n    (B) Changing the opening hours on weekdays.\n    (C) Making plans to help weekday morning business.\n    (D) Changing the time of the special sale on weekends.\n"}, "is_active": true, "auto_gradable": true, "difficulty": 3, "explanation": null}, {"id": "cap-108-english-reading-034", "exam_id": "cap", "subject_id": "